            <p class="eyebrow">What is pipe descaling?</p>
            <h2>A professional cleaning process for pipe interiors</h2>
            <p>Pipe descaling is a professional cleaning process designed to remove the buildup of scale, rust, and debris from pipe interiors. Over time, mineral deposits, grease, and waste materials create layers that narrow pipes and obstruct water flow. When left untreated, these blockages cause slow drainage, odors, and pipe damage.</p>
            <p>Honest Drain uses cutting-edge equipment to restore pipes to optimal condition. A flexible chain or carbide cutter on a high-torque cable scours the inside of the pipe back to bare iron. After descaling, a hydro jet flush carries the debris out and a camera confirms the cleaning. The line behaves like new pipe again without breaking through the floor.</p>
            <p class="link-row"><a class="text-link" href="../../../contact.html">Book a service visit</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="story-card">
            <strong>What this service covers</strong>
            <ul class="pill-list"><li>Cast iron stacks and branch lines</li><li>Rust tubercle removal</li><li>Mineral scale and grease buildup</li><li>Camera verification before and after</li><li>Hydro jet flushing as final step</li><li>Pipe lining preparation</li><li>Pre-descale assessment</li></ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section--muted">
        <div class="container split">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Warning signs</p>
            <h2>Signs your pipes need descaling</h2>
            <p>Common warning indicators that your pipes may need professional descaling include the following symptoms.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="callout-list">
            <div><strong>Slow draining sinks, tubs, or toilets</strong><span>Scale buildup is narrowing the pipe interior and restricting water flow.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Discolored or rusty water</strong><span>Yellow, brown, or cloudy water indicates active corrosion inside the pipes.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Frequent clogs that recur after snaking</strong><span>The rough, scaled pipe wall catches debris faster than a smooth pipe would.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Foul odors coming from drains</strong><span>Organic waste trapped in scale deposits decomposes and produces persistent smells.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Sewage backups into the home</strong><span>Severely restricted pipes can no longer handle normal waste volume.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Low water pressure from scale narrowing pipes</strong><span>Mineral deposits reduce the effective diameter and choke flow.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Leaking or corroded pipe joints</strong><span>Corrosion weakens joints and fittings, causing drips and moisture damage.</span></div>
            <div><strong>Gurgling, banging, or whistling pipe noises</strong><span>Air trapped by scale deposits or restricted flow creates unusual sounds.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">Common applications</p>
            <h2>When pipe descaling is the right solution</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="promise-grid">
            <article class="promise-card"><span>01</span><h3>Homes with cast iron pipes</h3><p>Pre-1980s construction with cast iron drain lines is the most common application. These pipes develop internal corrosion and scale over decades that only mechanical descaling can remove.</p></article>
            <article class="promise-card"><span>02</span><h3>Trenchless repair preparation</h3><p>Pipe descaling is an essential preparation step before pipe relining. The internal surface must be clean and smooth for the resin liner to bond properly and create a lasting repair.</p></article>
            <article class="promise-card"><span>03</span><h3>High-volume drain systems</h3><p>Commercial drains and sewer systems with heavy daily use accumulate scale faster. Regular descaling maintains flow capacity and prevents disruptive backups.</p></article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section--muted">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">Benefits</p>
            <h2>Benefits of pipe descaling</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Avoids costly replacements</h3><p>Descaling can delay or eliminate the need for complete pipe replacement, saving thousands compared to full re-piping. It extends the functional life of your existing drain system.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Improves drain performance</h3><p>Restoring the full internal diameter of the pipe brings back the original water flow capacity. Drains that have been sluggish for years can function like new again.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Eco-friendly and minimally invasive</h3><p>Descaling preserves existing infrastructure without excavation, demolition, or chemical treatments. It is the most environmentally responsible way to restore aging pipes.</p></div></article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">Our process</p>
            <h2>Step-by-step approach</h2>
            <p>The visit is structured so customers know what is happening and why. No surprises, no upsell pressure, no hidden line items.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Pre-descale camera inspection</h3><p>Confirm cast iron, locate scale buildup, and check for breaks or damage before mechanical work begins.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Descale mechanically</h3><p>A chain knocker or carbide cutter scours the inside of the pipe back to bare iron, removing all scale and corrosion.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Flush and clear debris</h3><p>Hydro jetting carries out the loosened debris and flushes the line clean.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>04</span><div><h3>Post-descale verification</h3><p>A camera confirms a smooth wall and documents the pipe condition. If breaks were found, repair options including pipe lining are explained without pressure.</p></div></article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

